annotationA: Mitochondrial import inner membrane translocase subunit TIM44; Essential component of the PAM complex, a complex required for the translocation of transit peptide-containing proteins from the inner membrane into the mitochondrial matrix in an ATP-dependent manner
annotationB: Hsc70Cb, isoform G; Hsc70Cb is an HSP110 family protein, and interacts physically with DnaJ-1 as a chaperone of misfolded proteins. Hsc70Cb functions together with DnaJ-1 to prevent the toxicity of aggregation-prone proteins
